SIMPLE: weeper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weeper
<hw>Weep"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
weeps; esp., one who sheds tears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A white band or border worn on the sleeve as a badge
of mourning.</def> <rj><au>Goldsmith.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The capuchin. See
<er>Capuchin</er>, 3 <sd>(a)</sd>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weepful</ent>⟦br⟧
